Excellent, easy, and fairly quick. I blanched the beans first for 20 seconds.I served this at a dinner party with scallops and everyone really liked it. One of the nicest things about the recipe is that all the ingredients can be prepped well ahead of time. I sauteed the shallots in the butter, chopped the beans and blanched them, and removed the corn kernels from the cob, and zested/juiced the limes before my guests arrived. Definitely will be on my table every August!

