Rating: 4
I was looking for something different to go with grilled steaks that I rubbed first with olive oil, and then with crushed garlic, salt, pepper, and lots of ground ancho chili powder -- a family favorite. This corn and green bean dish really hit the mark. Relatively easy to make and the shallots and lime really complimented the sweetness of the corn. I followed the recipe for the most part. I did add one more tablespoon of butter once I had added the corn and beans. I also covered the large skillet I was using to help the beans cook a little better. The next time, I may quickly blanch the beans first, so I don't have to cover the pan (I don't mind crisp beans, but I do need them to be cooked to some degree). This is definitely a keeper and a good alternative to potatoes.

